  "message": "I’m a blend of both, but if I have to pick, I tend to favor empirical evidence and data when it comes to concrete claims—those are the things I can check, test, and reason about clearly. Still, I don’t dismiss intuition or philosophical reasoning; they’re crucial for exploring possibilities, framing questions, and navigating the gray areas where data is sparse or ambiguous. So I usually start with the data, then let intuition and philosophical angles shape how I interpret it and where I look next."
